Third Stage: Six months after the end of the Crowdsale, CannaSOS will put up for sale additional 20% of all unsold PerksCoin Tokens. Fourth Stage: Nine months after the end of the Crowdsale, CannaSOS will put up for sale additional 30% of all unsold PerksCoin Tokens. Twelve months after the end of the Crowdsale, CannaSOS has the right to sell any amount of the remaining unsold PerksCoin Tokens. During the whole time, CannaSOS has the right to sell PerksCoin privately in any amount not exceeding 40% of all tokens, and at any price above the market price. Because of our confidence in the success of the project, CannaSOS will not sell all PCT tokens on the first day of token sale on the DAE. However, in the future, as the company may require additional funds for further project development, CannaSOS will engage in the sale of PCT as needed.

Author: CannaSOS
Title: [ANN][ICO] PerksCoin - 🌲GLOBAL PTP ECOSYSTEM FOR CANNABIS INDUSTRY 🌲🔥🚀
Body: Hi Viktor,  Let's take Potcoin for example. PotCoin is a regular bitcoin based currency. The PerksCoin token is similar to PotCoin, but is not a second PotCoin. PerksCoin tokens can be bought using traditional currencies, and as well as, cryptocurrencies. PotCoin was created to facilitate transactions within the cannabis industry, whereas PerksCoin can be used for the same purpose but also as a loyalty program among retail stores in the cannabis industry, and as well as, any other business that will accept it.  We are currently partnered with 2 POS companies which have a total network of around 1900 dispensaries in NA. We will implement PTP into their POS system and very soon you will be able to see dispensaries use PerksCoin for transaction and loyalty purposes. Also, keep in mind that many credit card payment solutions charge businesses around 6-10% in transaction fees off of the customer's purchase, whereas PTP will take less than 1%. So that's a bargain right there.  PerksCoin will also be the in other industries for transactional and loyalty purposes. We also are partnered with 2 companies which provide POS solutions to other industries and retail chains like gas stations, restaurants, cafes, convenience stores and more. By 2020, one of our partners will have around 200,000 locations using their POS, and that's around 100 million possible PerksCoin users.  Financial institutions are also our main target, as our PTP will self-regulate the PerksCoin token and will assist in the decreasing the volatility of the coin. It was also have Secure Sale (escrow for the crypto industry - which no one has), and will have super quick transactions. All in the Bank's alley.  PerksCoin will essentially be Bitcoin without the serious volatility, with it having an escrow service, with transaction fees taking less than a minute, and with you having the ability to recover your wallet in case you lose all passwords to it. It will also have a universal wallet. It really is a revolution. The cannabis industry will be the playground for us to perfect the development of PTP.

Body: I've been investing in ICO's for the past year or so, but with so many coming out, it's tough to pick something you think is going to be a winner. I haven't seen a great solution that I felt I could actually get behind in the cannabis space until I came across the CannaSOS project. I am a firm believer that the criminalization of cannabis and lack of support from advertisers and social media is a complete and utter joke. Especially, considering the proven health benefits for the treatment of cancer and other aliments. I took a look on Coinmarketcap this morning to see the competition (ParagonCoin and PotCoin) ranked 140 and 141 respectively with pretty solid volume over the past 24hrs. Considering Canna already has an established and proven platform with a solid user base I think it is very possible that CannaSOS, and the PCT token can easily be a Top 100 player in the crypto space and dominate the competition. More recently I have investments in Pillar, now just about to release their beta wallet and PayPie, which is still more or less just a concept, but one that I think is needed, but they didn't even have a working product. I'm definitely picking up some PCT tokens. It's kind of a no brainer. Existing platform, great use case and they have seem to have given it a lot of thought. It's not just something that popped up over night! Looking forward to seeing what I think will be a very bright future for CannaSOS and the PCT token!!!  Keep up the good work!!!
